
[1]tomentous

   TOMENT'OUS, a. [L. tomentum, down.] In botany, downy; nappy; cottony;
   or flocky; covered with hairs so close as scarcely to be discernible,
   or with a whitish down, like wool; as a tomentous stem or leaf.
